<br>
I can't really answer for the others' opinions on this subject, but the following is my opinion.  To request adding TAUNT ability to the bard class is (again, IMO) rouphly congruous to saying, &quot;I can see myself needing this ability so that I can plan to be MT&quot;.  Being MT, while ceratinly possible (heck, I've done it several times... even in LDoN when my group simply couldn't find any other viable candidate), isn't really that harmonious with the essence of what I feel defines the bard class.<br>
<br>
I know several will argue that haveing taunt will help them &quot;save&quot; the cleric/enchanter/necro when an add zooms past the tanks and starts wailing on them.  I, personally, would simply mezz it off them.  If the mob were DoT'ed, and I couldn't keep mezz consistently landed, chain mezzing or snaring will give the player enough time (usually) to get some distance so that somebody can root and/or off-tank the DoT'd add.  Nowhere in this scenario did I, as the bard, need TAUNT.<br>
<br>
