<br>
Here's the deal.  Sure, lots of things on the list are bugs.  But, I suppose, if the bard community is MOST bugged by a bug, then the developers should know. <br>
<br>
For instance, say they broke the ability to move and sing at the same time.  If Trem did his poll thing, he'd find that 100% of bards considered that the #1 issue, the devs would see that and do something.  Now, realistically, something that big would cause all hell to break loose, but you get the idea.<br>
<br>
The point is that even bugs have to get put on a developers 'todo' list.  Even if it's important, it won't get fixed if no one gets assigned to do it.  So, we vote, they find out that 'speeds up, slows down' is one of our big concerns and it eventually gets fixed. <br>
<br>
Tada! Magic.<br>
 <p>Wyndaria, <br>
Maestro, The Nameless.<br>
