<br>
I am not in favor of giving bards the Taunt ability.<br>
<br>
I am, however, in favor of an agro modifier or agro proc to be added to Johnathon's line of songs.  Particularly since one already has the name &quot;Provocation&quot;.  (This or similar has been suggested several times on these boards.)  This is the same item on the poll.<br>
<br>
While this isn't the TOP concern of mine, I can understand that it would be quite useful for level 40-60 bards to be able to build up agro when necessary if they are the only non-caster in a pickup group, or if the tank goes down or even goes AFK.  It is a method of long-term agro, not snap agro (like taunt or stuns give) that I'd like to see addressed.<br>
<br>
I remember at level 15 I could hold agro when duoing with similar level rogue with ease (before the invention of evade).  At level 57 I had difficulty holding agro off a level 53 ranger who was jolting and frequently turning off auto-attack.  Since most classes do more damage than they used to, SoS is not as large of a relative agro boost as it once was, nor are our slows.<br>
<br>
With the increase in melee damage provided in PoP levels, and with the introduction of the Thunderous Drums of Karana and the PoP chants, this seems to be somewhat less of an issue for PoP level bards.  At level 65, my melee alone is enough to allow players to heal me without drawing agro in LDoN and such (though maybe not if frequent healing is called for).  I still think it would be nice for bards of all levels to have one song that is particularly good at holding agro, and not have to drop all other jobs when trying to hold agro.<br>
<br>
End of Rambling.<br>
<br>
- Lall<br>
Bold Bardess with 113 Melodic Tools<br>
Shards of Avalon, Xegony. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eqarpeggio>EQArpeggio</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://cosx.com/eqarpeggio.gif width=102 height=178" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Honored sponsor</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#330000>(7/22/04 12:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19619.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://cosx.com/eqarpeggio.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: agro issues</span><hr size=1> Has there ever been any discussion on the giving everyone (not just bards) the ability to REMOVE an AA that you have purchased and wish you didn't have?<br>
