<br>
Here's the scenario, mobs inc, all mezzable, casters are debuffing like mad and raid is killing mobs one at a time.  We need to mez the rest.  Uber_Mob_001 is beating on a mage/shammy for debuffing it and I am casting mez.  I would much rather the mob be beating on me (with 1k-2k more hps and god knows how much more ac/avoidance, and the ability to cast while MOVING) than the poor caster who goes oom on a rez.  Do I want to be able to snap aggro to myself, yes, now more than ever I find my self wanting to offtank a mob for 5-10 seconds while a spell goes off.  Bards have been made into decent tanks but not aggro capabilities.<br>
<br>
Do I want to be able to out aggro a pally, ranger, SK, warrior, cleric?  No, I don't wanna be the best at it.  But I want to be able to snap aggro off of non tanking classes to resonable success.<br>
